{
  "stem": "12491.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Everybody in the ghetto had to have identification card and job assignment.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Otherwise, he was lost.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So actually, my brother started working on the airport before I did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was still working at the furriers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after June 6, when I realized that this assignment is not going to save me, I had to change my assignment.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went back to the friend-- my friends in the office.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was an [GERMAN] and I managed to get a change of assignment, also to the airport.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my younger brother and I were working at the airport, my sister was working for the dressmakers for the SS wives, and my mother was gone.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My older brother was left behind in Russia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, my-- my younger brother, when he came back, was smuggled in-- into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Told-- ?] I asked him, Manek, why did you come?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Where is Milek?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He said, Milek is dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Germans occupied Kiev-- well, after they actually-- after the liquidation of that farm in eastern Poland, the Russians moved all these people further east, and he wound up in Kiev.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know very little, if anything, about what he did in Kiev, where he lived in Kiev.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "All I know from our younger brother that when the Germans arrived, they assembled all the Jews and killed them, and my older brother was killed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is why my younger brother decided that he is not going to stay, he is going to go back home-- what he thought is home.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He did not know enough about ghetto to know that this is not home anymore, that he probably would have been better off trying to stay in Russia, maybe even going further east.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He probably would have been-- would have been alive today.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
